                                        <comments>
                            <comment id="12640764" author="yedingding@gmail.com" created="Sat, 18 Oct 2008 11:46:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The default numbers of rows is 1. So it will not affect the current apis.  User can add limit parma to the search string, such as /&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;tables&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;/scanner/&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;scanner_id&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;?limit=10.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The result will be &amp;lt;rows&amp;gt;&amp;lt;row&amp;gt;..&amp;lt;/row&amp;gt;&amp;lt;row&amp;gt;..&amp;lt;/row&amp;gt;..&amp;lt;/rows&amp;gt; if limit &amp;gt; 1, else &amp;lt;row&amp;gt;..&amp;lt;/row&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12640770" author="yedingding@gmail.com" created="Sat, 18 Oct 2008 13:20:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fix NullPointerException&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12640839" author="jdcryans" created="Sun, 19 Oct 2008 14:20:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Moved this into 0.19.0 since we don&apos;t release new features in 0.18.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, did you take a look at &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-887&quot; title=&quot;Fix a hotspot in scanners&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-887&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-887&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;? Can you confirm that there are no bad interactions between your patch and the current state of trunk? Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12640850" author="yedingding@gmail.com" created="Sun, 19 Oct 2008 17:05:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi, J-D.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the mention.  I haven&apos;t put the eyes on that before.  Will change using the new apis.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12643125" author="stack" created="Tue, 28 Oct 2008 04:31:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sishen: Are you going to update this patch to accomodate J-D&apos;s suggestion?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12643133" author="yedingding@gmail.com" created="Tue, 28 Oct 2008 04:45:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Stack: if accomodate J-D&apos;s suggestion, i think we must apply the patch of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-959&quot; title=&quot;Be able to get multiple RowResult at one time from client side&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-959&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-959&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; at first.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12643148" author="yedingding@gmail.com" created="Tue, 28 Oct 2008 05:50:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Accomodate J-D&apos;s suggestion.  And also add the new next(int nbRows) method to the Scanner interface.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12643297" author="stack" created="Tue, 28 Oct 2008 18:27:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sishen: It looks like you are just removing the next() and hasNext() from the REST Scanner rather than first deprecating it?  As is, if folks have written code that expects next(), they&apos;ll get a surprise.   Do they have to be removed?  If so, would suggest you instead deprecate them and then remove them in a later release &amp;#8211; 0.20.0. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12643300" author="yedingding@gmail.com" created="Tue, 28 Oct 2008 18:45:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes.  I reimplemented the ScannerRecord. But it&apos;s only used in ScannerHandler internally and i have changed all the logic.  is this ok?  Do I still need to deprecate it at first?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12643302" author="stack" created="Tue, 28 Oct 2008 18:52:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If all internal, no need to do deprecation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Applied.  Thanks for the patch Sishen.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
